{{Quote|I came here to settle a score, and I invoke the code to seek justice through single combat.|Sabine Wren|<ref name="The Protector of Concord Dawn">{{Rebels|The Protector of Concord Dawn}}</ref>}}
The '''Mandalorian code'''<ref name="Episode Gallery">{{SW|url=series/star-wars-rebels/the-protector-of-concord-dawn-episode-gallery|text="The Protector of Concord Dawn" Episode Gallery}} {{C|Slide 14}}</ref> was a code followed by traditional [[Mandalorian]] warriors that could be invoked to settle disputes via one-on-one combat. [[Sabine Wren]] used the code to challenge [[Fenn Rau]] to a duel after the [[Journeyman Protector|Protector]] had injured [[Hera Syndulla]] in a [[Dogfight over Concord Dawn|battle]] over [[Concord Dawn]].<ref name="The Protector of Concord Dawn" /> The individual known as "[[Frog Lady]]" thought honoring one's word was a part of the Mandalorian code.<ref name="Chapter 10">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 10: The Passenger}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The notion of a Mandalorian code was very common in [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], with various examples such as the [[Canons of Honor]], ''[[Resol'nare]]'', and [[Supercommando Codex]] established as having been introduced over the centuries of Mandalorian history.

